text: Arslano-Amekachevo () is a rural locality (a village) in Krivle-Ilyushkinsky Selsoviet, Kuyurgazinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 159 as of 2010. There are 5 streets. == Geography == It is located 28 km from Yermolayevo, 6 km from Krivle-Ilyushkino. == References == Category:Rural localities in Kuyurgazinsky District
title: Arslano-Amekachevo
